            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Any `&magic`-like option is a *major* breakage to many scripts, mappings, etc. Breaking many scripts is by no means “doing things right”: if I were Bram I would never allowed &magic, &gdefault, etc in first place without introducing a way for scripts to run with defaults yet edit user settings if needed: when you don’t care about backwards compatibility this task is much easier. I can imagine how this may be done without a major breakage even now, but it is far, far easier to write a plugin which imitates `&vmagic` option only for user (BTW, are not there some already?) without breaking any well-written (i.e. following “best practices” like “use [nxo]noremap in place of map”) scripts then to consistently code needed functionality in C.",
